    • Field Detail

      • FACE_IMAGE_NAME

        public static final java.lang.String FACE_IMAGE_NAME
        Name of the image sent to MetadataListener that contains face. This image will be sent to MetadataListener during recognition process if displaying of face image is enabled (see setShowFaceImage(boolean), and receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED image is enabled with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • FULL_DOCUMENT_IMAGE

        public static final java.lang.String FULL_DOCUMENT_IMAGE
        Name of the image sent to MetadataListener that contains full document. This image will be sent to MetadataListener during recognition process if displaying of full document image is enabled (see setShowFullDocumentImage(boolean), and receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED image is enabled with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • setShowFaceImage

        public void setShowFaceImage(boolean showFaceImage)
        Sets whether face image from ID card should be sent to MetadataListener. If enabled, image will be of type ImageType.DEWARPED, and the name of the image (see Image.getImageName()) will be equal to FACE_IMAGE_NAME, so make sure you subscribe to receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED images with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)
        Parameters:
        showFaceImage - whether face image should be sent to MetadataListener.

      • shouldShowFaceImage

        public boolean shouldShowFaceImage()
        Returns whether sending of face image from ID card to MetadataListener is enabled.
        Returns:
        whether sending of face image from ID card to MetadataListener is enabled.

      • setShowFullDocumentImage

        public void setShowFullDocumentImage(boolean showFullDocumentImage)
        Sets whether full document image should be sent to MetadataListener. If enabled, image will be of type ImageType.DEWARPED, and the name of the image (see Image.getImageName()) will be equal to FULL_DOCUMENT_IMAGE, so make sure you subscribe to receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED images with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)
        Parameters:
        showFullDocumentImage - whether full document image should be sent to MetadataListener.
